ثم تعود للجلسة التالية معنا بنشاط  جديد وسترى كيف تتحسن انتاجيتك و كفاءة مذاكرتك

S18.description:
Hellowzinho! 🥰

Keep me on the corner of your screen while you work in something else (another tab): double click with the right button on the video and select the option picture-in-picture! Doooone! Now we can stay together all the time! 😍

Nice to meet you and it's a pleasure to have your company here! 
My name is Brendha, I'm 27 years old and my dream is to become a doctor. 🩺❤️

🕑 Timezone: UTC - 3 (Horário de Brasília)

Q&A 👀

1. Where are you from?
I'm from Brazil 💚💛

2. What languages do you speak?
Portuguese and English

3. Who is Felipe Eduardo?
He's my husband ❤️

4. What are the names of your dogs?
We have five dogs: Moranga 🤍, Max 🧡, Mawi 🖤,  Morpheu 🖤🤍 and Fiapo 🧡🖤
It's because of them that I keep the rain backgroud sound and sometimes I have to turn off my mic... They have so much energy 🤪

5. When is your birthday?
July 30th

6. Did you study another course in college previously?
Yes, I studied Chemical Engineering for about 1 year and a half, but I decided to quit so I could focus in getting into med school, which was always my dream.

7. Are you already in med school?
Unfortunately, not yet. The entrance exam here in Brazil to get into med school is really hard and I've been preparing myself for it. I've got close, really close 😅, but it wasn't enough. So, right now, I'm studying for the entrance exam.

8. What is the meaning of 'bora'? 😄
'Bora' is a brazilian slang that we usually use when we want to say 'let's go!", so everytime we start a new session, we say BORA!!!! 😁 Very cheerful!

9. How does this study with me livestream work?
I'm here to help you to get motivated to study and to keep you company! Also, having your company here with me is super super super motivational, it helps me to get through the study day in a better way! ❤️ So, while I have online live classes, I won't take official breaks and I'll answer your messages whenever I can by the chat! During study sessions, we will study for 90 minutes (1h30)  or more and then take a break of 10 minutes, when we can rest and chat. During the day, I'll also may take long breaks to go to the gym, have lunch, take a shower, have dinner, do some chores (...), and the stream will keep going on during this time!

10. O que eu faço se sou brasileiro/brasileira?
Vem cá treinar esse inglês, meu bem!!!! Brincadeiras à parte, eu sempre falo em português com o pessoal e traduzo para o português o que estou falando em inglês quando há necessidade! Então, pode entrar e ficar à vontade, a casa é sua! 😁 E tenha certeza que seu inglês vai melhorar bastante se você praticar o listening (me ouvir) e o writing (escrever no chat) 😉

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose.
